abstract: Catalonia's far-left Popular Unity Candidacy party are deadlocked on whether or not to back Catalan leader Artur Mas; Mas promises to make Catalonia independent from Spain but needs party to support his re-election; party officials plan meeting to discuss deadlock but if no deal is reached by January 2016, new elections will be held.
lead_paragraph: An election to let Artur Mas, who lost a crucial vote last month, serve another term as the head of a coalition of parties supporting Catalonia’s secession yielded a deadlock on Sunday.

headline.main: Tied Vote on Catalan Separatist Leader in Spain
headline.print_headline: Tied Vote on Separatist Leader in Spain
